<subSubSection pageId="75" pageNumber="76" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1436,1277,1698]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1324948127" location="Van" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Van">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1421,1446]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[322,554,1421,1446]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis box="[322,554,1421,1446]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Chrysallida flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is herein identified according to the original description given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Monterosato" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" refString="Monterosato, T. A. di (1874) Recherches conchyliologiques, effectuees au Cap Santo Vito, en Sicile. Journal de Conchyliologie, 22 (3), 243 - 282, 22 (4), 359 - 364." type="journal article" year="1874">Monterosato (1874)</bibRefCitation>
and that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Micali" box="[357,638,1457,1482]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" refString="Micali, P. &amp; Nofroni, I. (2004) On the specific validity of Chrysallida penchynati (B. D. D., 1883) and description of Chrysallida rinaldii n. sp. Bollettino Malacologico, 39 (9 - 12), 177 - 180." type="journal article" year="2004">Micali &amp; Nofroni (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[648,866,1458,1482]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" refString="Van Aartsen, J. J. (1977) European Pyramidellidae: I. Chrysallida. Conchiglie, 13 (3 - 4), 49 - 64." type="journal article">
<collectingRegion box="[648,692,1458,1481]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Van</collectingRegion>
Aartsen (1977)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[986,1111,1457,1482]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pyramidellidae" genus="Chrysallida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis box="[986,1111,1457,1482]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">C. flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as possessing orthocline ribs and many spiral threads, thus probably misidentifying the specimens he had at hand.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1436,1277,1698]" box="[199,1207,1529,1554]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,339,1529,1554]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Occurrence</emphasis>
. Cores BC21 (2 specimens), BC51 (4), BC67 (2). Maximum height: 
<quantity box="[1114,1203,1529,1554]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
